    Photo: Ryan Pierse/Getty

block intro-description
  :marked
    Australia is a growing nation with a culturally diverse population. At the
    last census in 2016, more than a quarter (26%) of Australians were born
    overseas, and almost half (49%) had at least one overseas-born parent.
    Migration has made a steadily increasing contribution to Australia's
    population growth, and the challenge for government is to balance the
    economic and social benefits of migration with the effects of population
    growth on infrastructure and service&nbsp;delivery.

